Russ Gibb (June 15, 1931 – April 30, 2019) was an American concert promoter, and media personality from Dearborn, Michigan, best known for his role in the "Paul is dead" phenomenon, a story he broke as a disc jockey on radio station WKNR-FM in Detroit.
In 1965-66 Gibb was hired by The Methodist Church to host Night Call on the Mutual Broadcasting Network.

He returned to teaching and spent over 20 years teaching video and media production at Dearborn High School, which spawned the cable video show Back Porch Video.
